article.headline: Cornell 87, Yale 2 (OT)
article.story: ITHACA, N.Y. (AP) -- Lenny Collins scored 11 points in two overtime periods, including the game-tying three-pointer at the end of the first extra session, as Cornell beat Yale 87-82 in an Ivy League basketball game on Saturday night. Collins finished with 21 points for Cornell (9-10, 4-2). Ryan Rourke led the Big Red with 22 points and 12 rebounds. Eric Taylor and Cody Toppert each had 12 points. Edwin Draughan scored 25 points for Yale (5-12, 1-3), and Sam Kaplan added 12. The Bulldogs shot 51 percent from the field, but turned the ball over seven more times than Cornell.
